# 03 AuthN/AuthZ and Admin Controls

## Intent
Enforce strong identity, access control, and privileged-surface hardening.

## Mandatory
- MFA required for all admin and support operations.
- RBAC/ABAC enforced server-side for every protected action.
- Privileged actions require explicit purpose code and audit event.
- Session hardening: secure cookies/tokens, rotation, inactivity timeout, revocation.
- Quarterly privilege review for admin/service accounts.

## Admin Surface Rules
- Restrict admin endpoints by network controls and role checks.
- Separate break-glass workflows with time-bound elevation and full audit.

## Prohibited
- Shared admin accounts.
- Long-lived static credentials in code or config.
